        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 4:21PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 420 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Greenwood Lake, or near Warwick, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Yonkers, White Plains, New City, Bergenfield, Paramus, Ridgewood,
Monsey, Nanuet, Ramsey, Ringwood, Tarrytown, Dobbs Ferry, Suffern,
Nyack, and Warwick.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
southern Connecticut...northeastern New Jersey...and southeastern New
York.</instruction>
